-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
package sdid from http://fmwww.bc.edu/repec/bocode/s
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

TITLE
      'SDID': module to perform synthetic difference-in-differences estimation,
        inference, and visualization

DESCRIPTION/AUTHOR(S)
      
       The sdid command implements the synthetic
      difference-in-differences method of Arkhangelsky et al. (AER,
      2021) for Stata. The program generates the ATT estimate derived
      in Arkhangelsky et al. (2021), and conducts inference following
      their bootstrap, placebo, or jackknife methods. The command
      allows for multiple treatment dates and multiple treatment units
      directly, as well as cases with only a single treatment unit.  As
      well as estimation and inference, the sdid command includes a
      number of graphical output options to summarize the synthetic
      difference-in-differences estimator.
      
      KW: difference-in-differences
      KW: DiD
      KW: synthetic
      KW: Arkhangelsky
      
      Requires: Stata version 13
      
      Distribution-Date: 20240816
      
      Author: Daniel Pailañir, Universidad de Santiago de Chile
      Support: email dpailanir@fen.uchile.cl
      
      Author: Damian Clarke, Universidad de Santiago de Chile
      Support: email dclarke@fen.uchile.cl
      
      Author:  Diego Ciccia, Economics Department, Sciences Po
      Support: email  diego.ciccia@sciencespo.fr
      

INSTALLATION FILES                                 (type net install sdid)
      sdid.ado
      sdid.sthlp
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
(type ssc install sdid to install)

. display "ssc describe sdid return code = " _rc
ssc describe sdid return code = 0

